  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Up-scaling smallholder-led innovation and enterprise</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Many small tea and coffee farmers in Tanzania, Kenya and Uganda earn less than two US dollars a day, and some as little as 11 pence. Farmers often have good ideas about how to grow more crops and protect against the effects of climate change, but it can be hard to share those ideas or have enough money to put them into practice. This project will allow farmers to help each other, sharing the low-cost solutions they&#x2019;ve discovered themselves. It will strengthen producer organisations and co-ops so that farmers can deal with problems together, and use appropriate technology like radio and text messaging to reach other farmers. As women often face barriers in joining co-ops, the project will deliberately target women and women&#x2019;s groups so that they also benefit. The project will also offer affordable loans so that farmers can put these solutions into practice.</narrative>
  </description>
